hould retain its ''de facto'' independent status. Only controls a portion of its claimed territory.<!-- Republic was declared on 27 April, referendum was on 11 May -->\n|-\n| {{flag|Veneto}}\n| [[2014 Venetian independence referendum|2014]]\n| {{flag|Italy}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}\n| The referendum was conducted online and through self-organized voting booths by a private organization, [[Plebiscite 2013]], without voter verification, and without the cooperation of the Italian national or Venetian regional governments. 89% of residents voted to split from Italy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2586531/Venice-votes-split-Italy-89-citys-residents-opt-form-new-independent-state.html|title=Venice votes to split from Italy as 89% of the city's residents opt to form a new independent state|last=Roberts|first=Hannah|date=2014-03-21|website=Mail Online|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rt.com/news/venice-votes-independence-italy-585/|title=89% of Veneto residents vote for independence from Rome|last=|first=|date=2014-03-23|website=RT|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-10}}</ref> An official [[2017 Venetian autonomy referendum|referendum on Venetian autonomy]] took place on 22 October 2017, with 98% voting in favor of special autonomy for Veneto.\n|-\n| {{flag|Scotland}}\n| [[2014 Scottish independence referendum|2014]]\n| {{flag|United Kingdom}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{Yes}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag_of_Catalonia.svg}} [[Catalonia]] <!-- Uses the independence flag since this column is for the proposed state -->\n| [[2014 Catalan self-determination referendum|2014]]\n| {{flag|Spain}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Sint Eustatius}}\n| [[2014 Sint Eustatius status referendum|2014]]\n| {{flag|Netherlands}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{Yes}}\n|A majority voted for autonomy within the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]], but low turnout invalidated the result.\n|-\n| [[File:Bandeira do movimento O Sul \u00c9 o Meu Pa\u00eds.svg|20px]] [[South Region, Brazil|South Brazil]]\n| [[The South is My Country#First edition|2016]]\n| {{flag|Brazil}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}\n| Described as a \"Plebisul\", the turnout was only 2.91%.\n|-\n| {{flag|Puerto Rico}}\n| [[2017 Puerto Rican status referendum|2017]]\n| {{flag|United States}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| If a majority of voters selected the \"Independence/Free Association\" option, another independence referendum between those two options would've been held. However, a majority of voters voted for U.S. statehood.\n|-\n| {{flag|Kurdistan}}\n| [[2017 Kurdistan Region independence referendum|2017]]\n| {{flag|Iraq}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{No}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-41744376|title=Iraqi Kurds offer to 'freeze' independence referendum result|date=25 October 2017|accessdate=27 October 2017|publisher=[[BBC]]}}</ref>\n| {{No}} <!-- This is for recognition of the referendum, which was not recognized by Iraq, not potential recognition of a Kurdish state-->\n| The referendum also took place in the [[disputed territories of Northern Iraq]].\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag_of_Catalonia.svg}} [[Catalonia]]\n| [[2017 Catalan independence referendum|2017]]\n| {{flag|Spain}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{No}}<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-41785292 Catalonia independence: Spain takes charge of Catalan government] BBC News, 28 October 2017</ref>\n| {{No}}\n| The Parliament of Catalonia unilaterally declared the formation of a [[Catalan declaration of independence|Catalan Republic]] on 27 October 2017. The declaration was not recognized by the Government of Spain which continued to regard Catalonia as part of its sovereign territory and asserted direct control at the beginning of the workday on 30 October. On 31 October 2017 the Constitutional Court of Spain formally revoked the declaration with retroactive effect.<ref>http://www.huffingtonpost.es/2017/10/31/suspendida-la-declaracion-de-independencia-de-cataluna_a_23262184/</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Bandeira do movimento O Sul \u00c9 o Meu Pa\u00eds.svg|20px]] [[South Region, Brazil|South Brazil]]\n| [[The South is My Country#Second edition|2017]]\n| {{flag|Brazil}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{No}}\n| {{No}}\n| Second edition of the referendum described as a \"Plebisul\", the turnout was only 1.72%.\n|-\n|{{flag|New Caledonia}}\n|[[2018 New Caledonian independence referendum|2018]]\n|{{flag|France}}\n|{{No}}\n|{{No}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Bougainville}}\n| [[2019 Bougainvillean independence referendum|2019]]\n| {{nowrap|{{flag|Papua New Guinea}}}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{tba|Subject to negotiation}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/11/bougainville-referendum-region-votes-overwhelmingly-for-independence-from-papua-new-guinea|title=Bougainville referendum: region votes overwhelmingly for independence from Papua New Guinea|last=Lyons|first=Kate|date=2019-12-10|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-12-11|language=en}} The referendum is nonbinding and the leadership of Papua New Guinea and Bougainville will negotiate, while the PNG parliament will have the final say.</ref>\n| {{Yes}}\n| Held between 23 November to 7 December 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-papua-bougainville-idUSKCN1UV0QK|title=Bougainville agrees with PNG to delay independence vote till November|last=Mair|first=John|date=2019-08-05|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-08-05|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/396000/bougainville-referendum-now-set-to-be-held-on-23-november|title=Bougainville referendum now set to be held on 23 November|date=2019-08-05|website=Radio New Zealand|language=en-nz|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref> The vote was not binding and the Government of Papua New Guinea has the final say on what becomes of Bougainville as voters chose independence.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radionz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/384471/bougainville-referendum-not-binding-pm|title=Bougainville referendum not binding - PM|date=2019-03-11|website=Radio New Zealand|language=en-nz|access-date=2019-03-18}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Scheduled independence referendums==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n!Proposed State\n!Date\n!Current state\n!Recognition\n!Notes \n|-\n| {{flag|New Caledonia}}\n| [[2020 New Caledonian independence referendum|6 September 2020]]<ref>[https://guardian.ng/news/frances-new-caledonia-to-hold-independence-vote-in-2020/ France\u2019s New Caledonia to hold independence vote in 2020] The Guardian, 5 November 2019</ref>\n| {{flag|France}}\n| {{Yes}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Chuuk}}\n| [[2022 Chuukese independence referendum|March 2022]]<ref name=\"chuuk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-pacific-micronesia/chuuk-independence-vote-postponed-as-china-u-s-pacific-contest-builds-idUSKCN20L09G?il=0|title=Chuuk independence vote postponed as China-U.S. Pacific contest builds|website=Reuters|date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n| {{flag|Micronesia}}\n| {{Yes}}\n|Was scheduled for March 2020, but the Micronesian government announced that the vote had been postponed again.<ref name=\"chuuk\"/>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*[[Balkanization]]\n*[[Declaration of independence]]\n** [[Unilateral declaration of independence|Unilateral]]\n*[[Decolonization]]\n*[[Ethnic nationalism]]\n*[[Independence movement]]\n*[[Lists of active separatist movements]]\n*[[List of irredentist claims or disputes]]\n*[[List of proposed state mergers]]\n*[[List of sovereign states]]\n*[[List of territorial disputes]]\n*[[National liberation]]\n*[[Secession]]\n*[[Self-determination]]\n*[[Separatism]]\n*[[Sovereignty]]\n*[[Succession of states]]\n*[[Territorial integrity]]\n\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Independence referendums| ]]\n[[Category:Secession]]\n[[Category:Independence]]\n", "name_user": "Mikrob\u00f8lgeovn", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePast inde