{"title_page": "Toll roads in Norway", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n[[File:Norwegian-road-sign-765.0.svg|thumb|The Norwegian sign for toll road, road sign 765. The \"Kr\" symbol is added on direction signs on roads leading to toll stations. This is the only sign posted prior to the station itself except for in city areas where a new 560-zone sign is posted on city limits.]]\n\n'''Norway''' has a long history in road tolling to finance bridges, tunnels and roads. The cities [[Oslo]], [[Bergen]] and [[Trondheim]] introduced toll rings between 1986 and 1991 as a means to discourage urban traffic and to finance infrastructure projects around those cities.<ref>{{Citation|title=bompenger|date=2019-05-27|url=http://snl.no/bompenger|work=Store norske leksikon|language=no|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref> Today toll rings circumscribe Oslo, [[Kristiansand]], [[Stavanger]], [[Haugesund]], [[Bergen]], [[Ask\u00f8y]], [[Bod\u00f8]], [[Harstad]], [[Grenland]], [[F\u00f8rde]] and [[Trondheim]]. Besides toll rings, road tolls are installed to finance certain road projects, and often also on the existing road to discourage people from using it. Some tolls use [[congestion pricing]] and/or environmentally differentiated toll rates.\n\nPrime minister [[Solberg's Cabinet]] proposed a road toll reform with four parts - a reduction of toll road operators, separation of the toll service provision for tolls and ferry tickets from the toll road companies, an interest compensation scheme for toll road loans, and a simplification of the price and discount schemes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://samferdsel.toi.no/teknologi/etterlengtet-bompengereform-men-svarer-den-pa-fremtidens-utfordringer-article33685-801.html|title=Etterlengtet bompengereform, men svarer den p\u00e5 fremtidens utfordringer?|last=|first=|date=2017-08-01|work=Samferdsel|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== AutoPASS ==\nThe Norwegian [[electronic toll collection]] system is called [[Autopass|AutoPass]], and is administrated by the [[Norwegian Public Roads Administration]]. The only manual toll road left is the [[Atlantic Ocean Tunnel]]. The system involves the installation of a [[DSRC]] based radio [[transponder]]  operating at 5.8&nbsp;GHz (MD5885), originally supplied by the Norwegian companies [[Q-Free]] and [[Fenrits]], and since 2013 supplied by [[Kapsch]] and Norbit,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tu.no/artikler/her-er-den-nye-bompengebrikken/233814|title=Her er den nye bompengebrikken|work=Tu.no|access-date=2018-01-16|language=nb-NO}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.adressa.no/nyheter/okonomi/2016/10/21/Millionkontrakt-til-tr%C3%B8ndersk-elektronikkbedrift-13676273.ece|title=Millionkontrakt til tr\u00f8ndersk elektronikkbedrift|last=Lynum|first=Sissel|date=2016-10-21|work=adressa.no|access-date=2018-01-30|language=nb-NO}}</ref> on the [[windscreen]] of a vehicle, and to sign a contract with one of the toll service providers. With an AutoPASS contract it is also possible to use the tag in Denmark and Sweden on ferries and bridges through the [[EasyGo]] partnership.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.autopass.no/en/abouNort-autopass|title=About AutoPASS - AutoPASS|last=Enonic|website=www.autopass.no|language=en|access-date=2018-01-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://easygo.com/en/about-easygo/about-easygo|title=About EasyGo {{!}} EasyGo|website=easygo.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-30}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Norwegian-road-sign-792.30.svg|thumb|Road sign 792.30 indicates an automatic toll station. According to the latest template on road signage in automatic toll stations, this sign shall be posted on the toll station, and the only sign posted prior to passing the station itself is a \"Kr\" symbol that is added on the direction signs on roads leading to the toll station.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=2019|title=Ny mal for skilting i automatiske bomstasjoner (AB)|url=|journal=Vegdirektoratet|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>]]If a vehicle passes through a toll station without a valid transponder, a photograph is taken of the registration number. Norwegian-registered vehicles are invoiced directly by the toll road operators, and foreign vehicles are invoiced by Euro Parking Collection plc (EPC).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/q-a|title=Q&A - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref> If a foreign vehicle is driven though a toll that use environmentally differentiated toll rates, the highest rate will be charged unless the vehicle's Euro class and fuel type are registered with EPC. Registration is optional, but registering an EPC account (the scheme is called \"Visitors' Payment\") will, in addition to the avoidance of paying the highest fee in tolls with environmentally differentiated rates, normally reduce the time from the journey until an invoice is received. The account also gives access to the invoices, the possibility to register for e-mail delivery and to make the payment. \n\nIf driving a rental car, the renter should register the car to receive the invoice directly. If it is not registered, the invoice will be sent to the rental company (the  car owner). The company may add administration fees when collecting the amount from the renter. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/visitors-payment|title=Visitors' Payment - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\n=== Compulsory tag for heavy commercial vehicles over 3.5 tonnes ===\nAll vehicles that exceed {{convert|3.5|tonnes}} and are primarily used for business, or are registered to a business, government, county municipality or municipality, must have a valid toll tag/agreement when driving on Norwegian public roads.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/compulsory-tag/about-compulsory-tag?lang=en|title=About compulsory tag - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-07-19}}</ref>\n\n== Toll road operators ==\nA toll road operator, who has signed a toll charge agreement with [[Norwegian Public Roads Administration|Statens vegvesen]] is responsible for the financing of all toll roads in Norway.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/about-autopass/organization-of-autopass|title=About road tolls in Norway - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref> As a consequence of the toll reform, regional toll road operators, owned jointly by the [[Counties of Norway|counties]], have been created:\n\n* [[Bompengeselskap Nord|Bompengeselskap Nord AS]] ([[Nordland]] and [[Troms og Finnmark]])\n* [[Vegamot|Vegamot AS]] ([[M\u00f8re og Romsdal]] and [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]])\n* [[Ferde|Ferde AS]] ([[Agder]], [[Rogaland]] and [[Vestland]])\n* [[Vegfinans|Vegfinans AS]] ([[Innlandet]], [[Vestfold og Telemark]] and [[Viken (county)|Viken]])\n* [[Fjellinjen|Fjellinjen AS]] ([[Oslo]] and [[Viken (county)|Viken]])\n\n== Rates and discounts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Rate groups and tag discounts<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/payment/rates-and-discounts|title=Rates and Discounts - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n!\n!Rate group 1\n!Rate group 2\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \n|\n* Vehicles weighing up to {{Convert|3500|kg||abbr=}} \n* Vehicles in vehicle group M1, regardless of weight\n|\n* Vehicles heavier than {{Convert|3501|kg||abbr=}}\n* Exception vehicles in vehicle group M1 with a valid tag\n|-\n|For vehicles in vehicle group M1 with a weight exceeding {{Convert|3500|kg||abbr=}}, an electronic tag and valid contract is required.\n|Mandatory tag: Vehicles registered to companies, or vehicles used for commercial purposes are required to have an electronic tag and a valid contract.\n|-\n|'''Vehicle groups with environmentally differentiated toll rates'''\n|'''Rate group 1 is divided into:''' \n\n* [[Zero-emissions vehicle|zero-emissions vehicles]]\n* [[Plug-in hybrid|plug-in hybrids]] \n* [[Diesel engine|diesel]]\n* other ([[Gasoline|petrol]], [[Natural gas|gas,]] [[Ethanol fuel|ethanol]], etc.)\n|'''Rate group 2 is divided into:'''\n* [[Zero-emissions vehicle|zero-emissions vehicles]]\n* [[Plug-in hybrid|plug-in hybrids]]\n* [[European emission standards|Euro VI]]\n* [[European emission standards|Pre-Euro VI]]\n|-\n|'''General tag discount'''\n|20%\n|0%\n|}\nThrough the process of Prop. 1 S Appendix 2 / Innst. 13 S (2015-2016), [[Storting|the Storting]] has endorsed the government\u2019s proposal to introduce a new tariff and discount system for tolling projects. In the new system, there will be a standardization of discounts. Vehicles in pricing group 1 with electronic tag and valid agreement will automatically receive 20 per cent discount. Vehicles in rate group 2 will not get a discount.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/2018/11/change-of-pricing-and-discount-system-from-01-012-18/?lang=en|title=Change of pricing and discount system from 01.012.18 \u00bb Ferde|date=2018-11-28|website=Ferde|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-12}}</ref> Discount and other benefits is only given to vehicles with a valid tag/agreement, \"Visitors' Payment\" does not give the same benefits.\n\nIn a growing number of tolling projects, a toll fee for zero-emission vehicles for rate group 1 is introduced. Zero-emission vehicle is a collective name for electric cars and hydrogen cars, and the toll fee is maximum 50% of ordinary toll fee after discount (i.e. if the toll fee is 10 NOK, it costs 8 NOK for those with a valid tag/agreement. The toll fee for zero-emission vehicles can hence be maximum 4 NOK). The introduction of payment for zero-emission vehicles is done according to the instructions from Prop. 87 S (2017-2018) and local government. Payment of tolls as a zero-emission vehicle requires tag and a valid agreement. Without a tag and a valid agreement, zero-emission vehicles will be charged ordinary fare like other vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/ufaqs/what-is-a-zero-emission-vehicle/?lang=en|title=What is a zero-emission vehicle? \u00bb Ferde|website=Ferde|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-12}}</ref>\n[[File:Bompengestasjon.jpg|thumb|Oslo Toll Ring]]\n\n== Toll rings ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!City/Region\n!Package/Project\n!County\n!Toll road operator\n|-\n|Ask\u00f8y\n|Ask\u00f8ypakken\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Oslo and Akershus\n|[[Oslo Package 3|Oslopakke 3]]\n|Oslo, Viken\n|Fjellinjen AS\n|-\n|Bergen\n|Milj\u00f8l\u00f8ftet\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Bod\u00f8\n|Bypakke Bod\u00f8\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - Veipakke Salten AS\n|-\n|Nord-J\u00e6ren\n|Bymilj\u00f8pakken\n|Rogaland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Fredrikstad\n|Bypakke Nedre Glomma\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans Bypakke Nedre Glomma AS\n|-\n|F\u00f8rde\n|F\u00f8rdepakken\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Grenland\n|Bypakke Grenland\n|Vestfold og Telemark\n|Vegfinans Bypakke Grenland AS\n|-\n|Harstad\n|Harstadpakken\n|Troms og Finnmark\n|BPS Nord - Troms Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|[[Haugaland|Haugalandet]]\n|Haugalandspakken\n|Rogaland, Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Kristiansand\n|Samferdselspakke for Kristiansandsregionen\n|Agder\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|[[Nordhordland]]\n|Nordhordlandspakken \n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Trondheim\n|Milj\u00f8pakke Trondheim\n|Tr\u00f8ndelag\n|Vegamot AS\n|}\n[[File:Bomstasjon E18 Skinmo.jpg|thumb|AutoPass Toll station on E18]]\n\n== Public roads ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Road\n!\n!County\n!Toll road operator\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\" |{{Europavei|6}}\n|Helgeland north<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.e6helgeland.no/Om_prosjektet-4.aspx|title=Om prosjektet {{!}} BPS Nord \u2013 Nordland Bompengeselskap AS|website=www.e6helgeland.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\n* Korgen - Bolna\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - Nordland Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|Helgeland south<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n* Tr\u00f8ndelag county boundary-Korgfjellet\n* Kappskarmo-Bratt\u00e5sen-Lien\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - Nordland Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|Trondheim\u2013Stj\u00f8rdal<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vegamot.no/Om_bompengeprosjektene-1.aspx|title=Om bompengeprosjektene {{!}} E6 Trondheim - Stj\u00f8rdal {{!}} Vegamot AS|website=www.vegamot.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Tr\u00f8ndelag\n|Vegamot AS\n|-\n|\u00d8yer-Tretten, Tingberg, Oppland<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://e6oppland.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E6-Oppland|title=Om E6 Oppland {{!}} E6 Oppland AS|website=e6oppland.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E6 Oppland\n|-\n|[[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]] [[Svinesund Bridge]], \u00d8stfold<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://svinesundsforbindelsen.no/en/home/|title=The portal between Norway and Sweden|website=Svinesundsforbindelsen AS|language=en|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Viken\n|Svinesundsforbindelsen AS\n|-\n|Moss, Raukerud, \u00d8stfoldpakka, \u00d8stfold<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://ostfold.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-%C3%98stfold-Bompengeselskap|title=Om \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap {{!}} \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap AS|website=ostfold.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|Gardermoen-Biri, Akershus<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e6bompenger.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E6-Gardermoen-Moelv|title=Om E6 Gardermoen - Moelv {{!}} E6 Gardermoen-Moelv AS|website=e6bompenger.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans E6 Gardermoen-Moelv AS\n|-\n|Frya-Sjoa, Oppland<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e6ringebu-otta.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E6-Ringebu-Otta|title=Om E6 Ringebu-Otta {{!}} E6 Ringebu-Otta AS|website=e6ringebu-otta.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans Ringebu-Otta AS\n|-\n|[[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]] [[H\u00e5logaland Bridge]]<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.haalogalandsbrua.no/Om_prosjektet-3.aspx|title=Om prosjektet {{!}} BPS Nord \u2013 H\u00e5logalandsbrua AS|website=www.haalogalandsbrua.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - H\u00e5logalandsbrua AS\n|-\n|{{Jct|country=NOR|E|6|E|10}}\n|Tr\u00e6ldal - Leirvik<ref name=\":4\" />\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - H\u00e5logalandsbrua AS\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |{{Europavei|16}}\n|Bolstad, Vossapakko, Hordaland<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/vossapakko/|title=Bompenger Voss {{!}} AutoPass-brikke og avtale Vossapakko|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Kongsvinger-Slomarka, Hedmark<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://kongsvingervegen.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E16-Kongsvingervegen|title=Om E16 Kongsvingervegen {{!}} E16 Kongsvingervegen AS|website=kongsvingervegen.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E16 Kongsvingervegen AS\n|-\n|Bagn-Bj\u00f8rgo, Oppland<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e16oppland.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E16-Oppland|title=Om E16 Oppland {{!}} E16 Oppland AS|last=|first=|date=|website=e16oppland.vegfinans.no|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-01}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E16 Oppland AS\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |{{Europavei|18}}\n|\u00d8stfoldpakka, \u00d8stfold<ref name=\":3\" />\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|Gulli-Langangen, Vestfold<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e18vestfold.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E18-Vestfold-AS|title=Om E18 Vestfold AS {{!}} E18 Vestfold AS|website=e18vestfold.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Vestfold og Telemark\n|Vegfinans E18 Vestfold AS\n|-\n|Rugtvedt- D\u00f8rdal, Telemark\n|Vestfold og Telemark\n|Vegfinans E18 Telemark AS\n|-\n|Tvedestrand - Arendal<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/2019/06/oppstart-innkreving-av-bompenger-for-e18-tvedestrand-arendal-02-07-19/|title=Oppstart innkreving av bompenger for E18 Tvedestrand-Arendal den 02.07.19 \u00bb Ferde|date=2019-06-04|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-06-04}}</ref> \n|Agder\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{Europavei|134}}\n|[[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]][[Stordal Tunnel]], \u00c5krafjorden<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/e134akrafjorden/|title=Bompenger \u00c5krafjorden {{!}} AutoPass-brikke og avtale Hordaland|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{Europavei|136}}\n|[[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]] [[Tresfjord Bridge]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eksportvegen.no/hvordan-fungerer-det/|title=Eksportvegen AS {{!}} Hvordan fungerer det?|website=www.eksportvegen.no|access-date=2019-11-10}}</ref>\n|M\u00f8re og Romsdal\n|Vegamot AS\n|-\n|{{jct|country=NOR|Rv|4}}\n|Dynna, Lunner boundary, Oppland<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://rv4oppland.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-Vegfinans-Rv4-Oppland|title=Om Vegfinans Rv4 Oppland {{!}} Rv4 Oppland AS|website=rv4oppland.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans Rv4 Oppland\n|-\n|{{jct|country=NOR|Rv|7}}\n|Sokna-\u00d8rgenvika, Buskerud<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hallingporten.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-Hallingporten|title=Om Hallingporten {{!}} Hallingporten AS|website=hallingporten.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans Hallingporten AS\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |{{jct|country=NOR|Rv|13}}\n|[[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]] [[Hardanger Bridge]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/hardangerbrua/|title=Hardangerbrua \u00bb Ferde|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Svelgane, Vossapakko<ref name=\":5\" />\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|[[Ryfylke Tunnel]], [[Ryfast]]<ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/2020/03/kunngjoring-oppstart-av-bompengeinnkreving-pa-rv-13-ryfast-den-30-03-20/|title=Kunngj\u00f8ring: Oppstart av bompengeinnkreving p\u00e5 rv. 13 Ryfast den 30.03.20 \u00bb Ferde|date=2020-03-04|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> (from after easter 2020)\n|Rogaland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|[[Hundv\u00e5g Tunnel]], Ryfast<ref name=\":12\" /> (from after easter 2020)\n|Rogaland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{jct|country=NOR|Rv|36}}\n|Sl\u00e5ttek\u00e5s\u2013\u00c5rnes, Ullevik<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rv36telemark.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-Vegfinans-Rv36-Telemark|title=Om Vegfinans Rv36 Telemark {{!}} Rv36 Telemark AS|website=rv36telemark.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Vestfold og Telemark\n|Vegfinans Rv36 Telemark\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{jct|country=NOR|Rv|80}}\n|[[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]]Tverland Bridge, L\u00f8ding - Vikan (Until 2020-04-01)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.veipakkesalten.no/Om_oss/Nyheter-13.aspx?Action=1&NewsId=372&M=NewsV2&PID=4063|title=Stanser innkreving av bompenger p\u00e5 Tverlandsbrua fra 1.april {{!}} BPS Nord \u2013 Veipakke Salten AS|website=www.veipakkesalten.no|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - Veipakke Salten AS\n|-\n|Fauske - Bod\u00f8<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.veipakkesalten.no/Om_prosjektet-5.aspx|title=Om prosjektet {{!}} BPS Nord \u2013 Veipakke Salten AS|website=www.veipakkesalten.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - Veipakke Salten AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|33}}\n|Skreifjella - Totenvika, Oppland<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fv33oppland.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-Vegfinans-Fv33-Oppland|title=Om Vegfinans Fv33 Oppland {{!}} Fv33 Oppland AS|website=fv33oppland.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans Fv33 Oppland\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|34}}\n|Grime-Vesleelva, Oppland<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fv34oppland.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-Fv34-Oppland|title=Om Fv34 Oppland {{!}} Fv34 Oppland AS|website=fv34oppland.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans Fv34 Oppland\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Fylkesvei|49}}\n|Kvammapakken, Hordaland<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/kvammapakken/|title=Bompenger Kvam {{!}} AutoPass-brikke og avtale Kvampakken|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\n* Steinsdalen\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|[[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]] [[Jondal Tunnel]], Hordaland<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/jondalstunnelen/|title=Bompenger Jondalstunnelen {{!}} AutoPass-brikke og avtale|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|64}}\n|[[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]] [[Atlantic Ocean Tunnel]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.atlanterhavstunnelen.no/|title=Atlanterhavstunnelen AS {{!}}|website=www.atlanterhavstunnelen.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|M\u00f8re og Romsdal\n|Atlanterhavstunnelen AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|78}}\n|[[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]] [[Toven Tunnel]], Vefsn, Vegpakke Helgeland<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.veipakkehelgeland.no/Om_prosjektet-6.aspx|title=Om prosjektet {{!}} BPS Nord \u2013 Helgeland veiutvikling AS|website=www.veipakkehelgeland.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - Helgeland Veiutvikling AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|79}}\n|Kvammapakken, Hordaland<ref name=\":7\" />\n\n* Kjepsoh\u00f8gda\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|118}}\n|[[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]] The old Svinesund Bridge, \u00d8stfold<ref name=\":2\" />\n|Viken\n|Svinesundsforbindelsen AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|128}}\n|Old E18, \u00d8stfoldpakka<ref name=\":3\" />\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|175}}\n|\u00c5sum, Kongsvinger-Slomarka, Hedmark<ref name=\":6\" />\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E16 Kongsvingervegen AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|198}}\n|Fulu, Kongsvinger-Slomarka, Hedmark<ref name=\":6\" />\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E16 Kongsvingervegen AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|255}}\n|F\u00e5berg, Gausdalsvegen, Oppland<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://gausdalsvegen.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-Gausdalsvegen|title=Om Gausdalsvegen {{!}} Gausdalsvegen AS|website=gausdalsvegen.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans Gausdalsvegen AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|316}}\n|Kambo, \u00d8stfoldpakka<ref name=\":3\" />\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|450}}\n|\u00d8vstab\u00f8, Gjesdal<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/gjesdal/|title=Bompenger Gjesdal {{!}} AutoPass-brikke og avtale Gjesdal|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Rogaland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|519}}\n|[[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]] [[Finn\u00f8y Tunnel]], Rennes\u00f8y<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/finnfast/|title=Bompenger E6 Finnfast {{!}} AutoPass-brikke og avtale Finnfast|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Rogaland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|542}}\n|[[B\u00f8mla Bridge|B\u00f8mlo Bridge]], B\u00f8mlopakken, Hordaland<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/kart/bomlopakken/|title=B\u00f8mlopakken \u00bb Ferde|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|553}}\n|[[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]] [[T-Link]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/tforbindelsen/|title=Bompenger T-Forbindelsen {{!}} Haugaland Bompengeselskap|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Rogaland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|714}}\n|Laksevegen<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vegamot.no/Om_prosjektet.aspx|title=Om prosjektet {{!}} Fv 714 Lakseveien {{!}} Vegamot AS|website=www.vegamot.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Tr\u00f8ndelag\n|Vegamot AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|715}}\n|Krinsvatn, Fosenpakken<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fosenvegene.no/|title=Fosenvegene.no {{!}} ei tim\u00b4 te\u00b4 by\u00b4n|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Tr\u00f8ndelag\n|Fosenvegene AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|858}}\n|[[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]] [[Rya Tunnel]], Troms\u00f8<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ryaforbindelsen.no/om-oss/|title=Om oss \u2013 Ryaforbindelsen|website=www.ryaforbindelsen.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Troms og Finnmark\n|Ryaforbindelsen AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|2300}}\n|Dynna, Lunner boundary, Oppland<ref name=\":9\" /> \n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans Rv4 Oppland AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|2450}}\n|Bagn-Bj\u00f8rgo, Oppland\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E16 Oppland\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Fylkesvei|2522}}\n|Frya-Sjoa, Oppland<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e6ringebu-otta.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E6-Ringebu-Otta|title=Om E6 Ringebu-Otta {{!}} E6 Ringebu-Otta AS|website=e6ringebu-otta.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans Ringebu-Otta AS\n|-\n|Skarsmoen, Oppland<ref name=\":1\" />\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E6 Oppland\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|2528}}\n|J\u00f8rstadmoen, Lundg\u00e5rd, Gausdalsvegen, Oppland<ref name=\":11\" />\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans Gausdalsvegen AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|5981}}\n|Around Tresfjorden, Eksportvegen<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/eksportvegen/|title=Bompenger Eksportvegen {{!}} AutoPass-brikke og avtale|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|M\u00f8re og Romsdal\n|Vegamot AS\n|}\n\n== Ferries collecting road tolls ==\nThe following ferry crossings collect road tolls as a surcharge to the ferry ticket:<ref>{{Kilde www|url=https://www.autopassferje.no/kundeservice/|tittel=Sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l og svar|bes\u00f8ksdato=2019-02-28|spr\u00e5k=nb-NO|verk=AutoPASS-ferje}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Road\n![[File:Ferry_icon.png|24x24px]]Crossing\n!County\n!Ferry operator\n!Toll road operator \n|-\n|{{Europavei|39}}\n|Mortavika\u2013Arsv\u00e5gen \n|Rogaland\n|[[Fjord1]]\n|\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|48}}\n|Gjermundshamn\u2013Varalds\u00f8y\u2013\u00c5rsnes\n|Vestland\n|[[Norled]]\n|\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|541}}\n|Langev\u00e5g\u2013Buav\u00e5g\n|Vestland\n|[[Norled]]\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Fylkesvei|546}}\n|Husavik\u2013Sandvikv\u00e5g\n|Vestland\n|[[Fjord1]]\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Krokeide\u2013Hufthamar\n|Vestland\n|[[Fjord1]]\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|710}}\n|Brekstad\u2013Valset\n|Tr\u00f8ndelag\n|[[Fjord1]]\n|Fosenvegene AS\n|-\n|{{Fylkesvei|715}}\n|Flakk\u2013R\u00f8rvik\n|Tr\u00f8ndelag\n|ATB\n|Fosenvegene AS\n|}\nMany crossings without toll charges also uses AutoPass as payment through the \"AutoPass for ferry\" concept.<ref>{{Kilde www|url=https://www.autopass.no/Betaling/ferjer|tittel=Ferjer - AutoPASS|bes\u00f8ksdato=2019-01-06|verk=www.autopass.no}}</ref> AutoPass customers with a valid agreement and tag, but without a separate ferry account gets a 10% discount in ferry crossings taking payment with the AutoPass tag. By making a prepayment into an Autopass ferry account, you get a 50% (40% corporate) discount for vehicle, and 17% for passengers at manual payment crossings.\n\n== Former Toll roads, tunnels and bridges ==\n\n* T\u00f8nsberg Toll Ring\n*Namsos Toll Ring \n* E6 Grillstad\u2013V\u00e6rnes\n* E6 Trondheim \u2013 Stj\u00f8rdal\n* E10/Fv82 Vester\u00e5l Bridges\n* E16 Hadelandsvegen\n*E16 F\u00f8nhus-Bagn\n* E18 Buskerud\n* E18 Vestfold Nord\n* E18 Agder\n*E39 Handeland, Listerpakken\n* E39 [[Rennes\u00f8y Fixed Link]]\n* E39 [[Triangle Link]]\n* E39 [[Nordhordland Bridge]]\n* E39 \u00d8ysand\u2013Thamshavn\n* E69 FATIMA-project\n* E134 [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]][[Oslofjord Tunnel]]\n* Rv4 Oppland\n* Rv5 [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]]Berg Tunnel and [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]][[Frudal Tunnel]]\n* Rv5 [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]][[Naustdal Tunnel|Naustdal tunnel]]\n*[[Norwegian National Road 9|Rv 9 Setesdal]]\n* Rv15 [[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]][[M\u00e5l\u00f8y Bridge]]\n* Rv19 Skoppum, Horten, Vestfold\n* Rv55 [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]]Fatla tunnel\n* Rv658 \u00c5lesund - Giske\n*Fv17 God\u00f8ystraumen<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.veipakkesalten.no/Om_oss/Nyheter-13.aspx?Action=1&NewsId=283&M=NewsV2&PID=4063|title=Bomstasjon God\u00f8ystraumen avsluttes. {{!}} BPS Nord \u2013 Veipakke Salten AS|website=www.veipakkesalten.no|access-date=2019-09-04}}</ref> \n*Fv43 Kollevoll, Listerpakken\n* Fv64 Sk\u00e5lavegen\n* Fv64 [[Atlantic Ocean Road]]\n* Fv71 [[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]][[Sykkylven Bridge]]\n* Fv108 [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]][[Hvaler Tunnel]]\n* Fv207 [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]][[Bjor\u00f8y Tunnel]]\n*Fv465 Gjervollstad, Listerpakken\n*Fv544 [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]] [[Halsn\u00f8y Tunnel]], Halsn\u00f8ysambandet \n* Fv551 [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]][[Folgefonna Tunnel|Folgefonna tunnel]]\n* Fv562 [[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]][[Ask\u00f8y Bridge]]\n* Fv566 [[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]][[Oster\u00f8y Bridge]]\n* Fv661 [[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]]Straumsbrua\n* Fv714 Sandstad ([[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]][[Hitra Tunnel]], [[File:Tunnel.png|24x24px]][[Fr\u00f8ya Tunnel]]<nowiki/> and Fjellv\u00e6r\u00f8yforbindelsen)\n* Fv755 [[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]][[Skarnsund Bridge]]\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Autopass|AutoPass]]\n*[[Dedicated Short Range Communications]]\n* [[Toll road]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.Autopass.no/Visitors English version of Official site]\n* [http://www.tolltickets.com/country/scandinavia/Autopass.aspx?lang=en-GB More information about Autopass]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Road transport in Norway]]\n[[Category:Toll roads in Norway]]\n[[Category:Wireless locating]]\n[[Category:Car costs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n[[File:Norwegian-road-sign-765.0.svg|thumb|The Norwegian sign for toll road, road sign 765. The \"Kr\" symbol is added on direction signs on roads leading to toll stations. This is the only sign posted prior to the station itself except for in city areas where a new 560-zone sign is posted on city limits.]]\n\n'''Norway''' has a long history in road tolling to finance bridges, tunnels and roads. The cities [[Oslo]], [[Bergen]] and [[Trondheim]] introduced toll rings between 1986 and 1991 as a means to discourage urban traffic and to finance infrastructure projects around those cities.<ref>{{Citation|title=bompenger|date=2019-05-27|url=http://snl.no/bompenger|work=Store norske leksikon|language=no|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref> Today toll rings circumscribe Oslo, [[Kristiansand]], [[Stavanger]], [[Haugesund]], [[Bergen]], [[Ask\u00f8y]], [[Bod\u00f8]], [[Harstad]], [[Grenland]], [[F\u00f8rde]] and [[Trondheim]]. Besides toll rings, road tolls are installed to finance certain road projects, and often also on the existing road to discourage people from using it. Some tolls use [[congestion pricing]] and/or environmentally differentiated toll rates.\n\nPrime minister [[Solberg's Cabinet]] proposed a road toll reform with four parts - a reduction of toll road operators, separation of the toll service provision for tolls and ferry tickets from the toll road companies, an interest compensation scheme for toll road loans, and a simplification of the price and discount schemes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://samferdsel.toi.no/teknologi/etterlengtet-bompengereform-men-svarer-den-pa-fremtidens-utfordringer-article33685-801.html|title=Etterlengtet bompengereform, men svarer den p\u00e5 fremtidens utfordringer?|last=|first=|date=2017-08-01|work=Samferdsel|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== AutoPASS ==\nThe Norwegian [[electronic toll collection]] system is called [[Autopass|AutoPass]], and is administrated by the [[Norwegian Public Roads Administration]]. The only manual toll road left is the [[Atlantic Ocean Tunnel]]. The system involves the installation of a [[DSRC]] based radio [[transponder]]  operating at 5.8&nbsp;GHz (MD5885), originally supplied by the Norwegian companies [[Q-Free]] and [[Fenrits]], and since 2013 supplied by [[Kapsch]] and Norbit,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tu.no/artikler/her-er-den-nye-bompengebrikken/233814|title=Her er den nye bompengebrikken|work=Tu.no|access-date=2018-01-16|language=nb-NO}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.adressa.no/nyheter/okonomi/2016/10/21/Millionkontrakt-til-tr%C3%B8ndersk-elektronikkbedrift-13676273.ece|title=Millionkontrakt til tr\u00f8ndersk elektronikkbedrift|last=Lynum|first=Sissel|date=2016-10-21|work=adressa.no|access-date=2018-01-30|language=nb-NO}}</ref> on the [[windscreen]] of a vehicle, and to sign a contract with one of the toll service providers. With an AutoPASS contract it is also possible to use the tag in Denmark and Sweden on ferries and bridges through the [[EasyGo]] partnership.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.autopass.no/en/abouNort-autopass|title=About AutoPASS - AutoPASS|last=Enonic|website=www.autopass.no|language=en|access-date=2018-01-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://easygo.com/en/about-easygo/about-easygo|title=About EasyGo {{!}} EasyGo|website=easygo.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-30}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Norwegian-road-sign-792.30.svg|thumb|Road sign 792.30 indicates an automatic toll station. According to the latest template on road signage in automatic toll stations, this sign shall be posted on the toll station, and the only sign posted prior to passing the station itself is a \"Kr\" symbol that is added on the direction signs on roads leading to the toll station.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=2019|title=Ny mal for skilting i automatiske bomstasjoner (AB)|url=|journal=Vegdirektoratet|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>]]If a vehicle passes through a toll station without a valid transponder, a photograph is taken of the registration number. Norwegian-registered vehicles are invoiced directly by the toll road operators, and foreign vehicles are invoiced by Euro Parking Collection plc (EPC).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/q-a|title=Q&A - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref> If a foreign vehicle is driven though a toll that use environmentally differentiated toll rates, the highest rate will be charged unless the vehicle's Euro class and fuel type are registered with EPC. Registration is optional, but registering an EPC account (the scheme is called \"Visitors' Payment\") will, in addition to the avoidance of paying the highest fee in tolls with environmentally differentiated rates, normally reduce the time from the journey until an invoice is received. The account also gives access to the invoices, the possibility to register for e-mail delivery and to make the payment. \n\nIf driving a rental car, the renter should register the car to receive the invoice directly. If it is not registered, the invoice will be sent to the rental company (the  car owner). The company may add administration fees when collecting the amount from the renter. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/visitors-payment|title=Visitors' Payment - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\n=== Compulsory tag for heavy commercial vehicles over 3.5 tonnes ===\nAll vehicles that exceed {{convert|3.5|tonnes}} and are primarily used for business, or are registered to a business, government, county municipality or municipality, must have a valid toll tag/agreement when driving on Norwegian public roads.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/compulsory-tag/about-compulsory-tag?lang=en|title=About compulsory tag - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-07-19}}</ref>\n\n== Toll road operators ==\nA toll road operator, who has signed a toll charge agreement with [[Norwegian Public Roads Administration|Statens vegvesen]] is responsible for the financing of all toll roads in Norway.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/about-autopass/organization-of-autopass|title=About road tolls in Norway - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref> As a consequence of the toll reform, regional toll road operators, owned jointly by the [[Counties of Norway|counties]], have been created:\n\n* [[Bompengeselskap Nord|Bompengeselskap Nord AS]] ([[Nordland]] and [[Troms og Finnmark]])\n* [[Vegamot|Vegamot AS]] ([[M\u00f8re og Romsdal]] and [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]])\n* [[Ferde|Ferde AS]] ([[Agder]], [[Rogaland]] and [[Vestland]])\n* [[Vegfinans|Vegfinans AS]] ([[Innlandet]], [[Vestfold og Telemark]] and [[Viken (county)|Viken]])\n* [[Fjellinjen|Fjellinjen AS]] ([[Oslo]] and [[Viken (county)|Viken]])\n\n== Rates and discounts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Rate groups and tag discounts<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autopass.no/en/payment/rates-and-discounts|title=Rates and Discounts - AutoPASS|website=www.autopass.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n!\n!Rate group 1\n!Rate group 2\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \n|\n* Vehicles weighing up to {{Convert|3500|kg||abbr=}} \n* Vehicles in vehicle group M1, regardless of weight\n|\n* Vehicles heavier than {{Convert|3501|kg||abbr=}}\n* Exception vehicles in vehicle group M1 with a valid tag\n|-\n|For vehicles in vehicle group M1 with a weight exceeding {{Convert|3500|kg||abbr=}}, an electronic tag and valid contract is required.\n|Mandatory tag: Vehicles registered to companies, or vehicles used for commercial purposes are required to have an electronic tag and a valid contract.\n|-\n|'''Vehicle groups with environmentally differentiated toll rates'''\n|'''Rate group 1 is divided into:''' \n\n* [[Zero-emissions vehicle|zero-emissions vehicles]]\n* [[Plug-in hybrid|plug-in hybrids]] \n* [[Diesel engine|diesel]]\n* other ([[Gasoline|petrol]], [[Natural gas|gas,]] [[Ethanol fuel|ethanol]], etc.)\n|'''Rate group 2 is divided into:'''\n* [[Zero-emissions vehicle|zero-emissions vehicles]]\n* [[Plug-in hybrid|plug-in hybrids]]\n* [[European emission standards|Euro VI]]\n* [[European emission standards|Pre-Euro VI]]\n|-\n|'''General tag discount'''\n|20%\n|0%\n|}\nThrough the process of Prop. 1 S Appendix 2 / Innst. 13 S (2015-2016), [[Storting|the Storting]] has endorsed the government\u2019s proposal to introduce a new tariff and discount system for tolling projects. In the new system, there will be a standardization of discounts. Vehicles in pricing group 1 with electronic tag and valid agreement will automatically receive 20 per cent discount. Vehicles in rate group 2 will not get a discount.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/2018/11/change-of-pricing-and-discount-system-from-01-012-18/?lang=en|title=Change of pricing and discount system from 01.012.18 \u00bb Ferde|date=2018-11-28|website=Ferde|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-12}}</ref> Discount and other benefits is only given to vehicles with a valid tag/agreement, \"Visitors' Payment\" does not give the same benefits.\n\nIn a growing number of tolling projects, a toll fee for zero-emission vehicles for rate group 1 is introduced. Zero-emission vehicle is a collective name for electric cars and hydrogen cars, and the toll fee is maximum 50% of ordinary toll fee after discount (i.e. if the toll fee is 10 NOK, it costs 8 NOK for those with a valid tag/agreement. The toll fee for zero-emission vehicles can hence be maximum 4 NOK). The introduction of payment for zero-emission vehicles is done according to the instructions from Prop. 87 S (2017-2018) and local government. Payment of tolls as a zero-emission vehicle requires tag and a valid agreement. Without a tag and a valid agreement, zero-emission vehicles will be charged ordinary fare like other vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/ufaqs/what-is-a-zero-emission-vehicle/?lang=en|title=What is a zero-emission vehicle? \u00bb Ferde|website=Ferde|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-12}}</ref>\n[[File:Bompengestasjon.jpg|thumb|Oslo Toll Ring]]\n\n== Toll rings ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!City/Region\n!Package/Project\n!County\n!Toll road operator\n|-\n|Ask\u00f8y\n|Ask\u00f8ypakken\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Oslo and Akershus\n|[[Oslo Package 3|Oslopakke 3]]\n|Oslo, Viken\n|Fjellinjen AS\n|-\n|Bergen\n|Milj\u00f8l\u00f8ftet\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Bod\u00f8\n|Bypakke Bod\u00f8\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - Veipakke Salten AS\n|-\n|Nord-J\u00e6ren\n|Bymilj\u00f8pakken\n|Rogaland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Fredrikstad\n|Bypakke Nedre Glomma\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans Bypakke Nedre Glomma AS\n|-\n|F\u00f8rde\n|F\u00f8rdepakken\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Grenland\n|Bypakke Grenland\n|Vestfold og Telemark\n|Vegfinans Bypakke Grenland AS\n|-\n|Harstad\n|Harstadpakken\n|Troms og Finnmark\n|BPS Nord - Troms Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|[[Haugaland|Haugalandet]]\n|Haugalandspakken\n|Rogaland, Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Kristiansand\n|Samferdselspakke for Kristiansandsregionen\n|Agder\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|[[Nordhordland]]\n|Nordhordlandspakken \n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Trondheim\n|Milj\u00f8pakke Trondheim\n|Tr\u00f8ndelag\n|Vegamot AS\n|}\n[[File:Bomstasjon E18 Skinmo.jpg|thumb|AutoPass Toll station on E18]]\n\n== Public roads ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Road\n!\n!County\n!Toll road operator\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\" |{{Europavei|6}}\n|Helgeland north<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.e6helgeland.no/Om_prosjektet-4.aspx|title=Om prosjektet {{!}} BPS Nord \u2013 Nordland Bompengeselskap AS|website=www.e6helgeland.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\n* Korgen - Bolna\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - Nordland Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|Helgeland south<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n* Tr\u00f8ndelag county boundary-Korgfjellet\n* Kappskarmo-Bratt\u00e5sen-Lien\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - Nordland Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|Trondheim\u2013Stj\u00f8rdal<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vegamot.no/Om_bompengeprosjektene-1.aspx|title=Om bompengeprosjektene {{!}} E6 Trondheim - Stj\u00f8rdal {{!}} Vegamot AS|website=www.vegamot.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Tr\u00f8ndelag\n|Vegamot AS\n|-\n|\u00d8yer-Tretten, Tingberg, Oppland<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://e6oppland.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E6-Oppland|title=Om E6 Oppland {{!}} E6 Oppland AS|website=e6oppland.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E6 Oppland\n|-\n|[[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]] [[Svinesund Bridge]], \u00d8stfold<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://svinesundsforbindelsen.no/en/home/|title=The portal between Norway and Sweden|website=Svinesundsforbindelsen AS|language=en|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Viken\n|Svinesundsforbindelsen AS\n|-\n|Moss, Raukerud, \u00d8stfoldpakka, \u00d8stfold<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://ostfold.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-%C3%98stfold-Bompengeselskap|title=Om \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap {{!}} \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap AS|website=ostfold.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|Gardermoen-Biri, Akershus<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e6bompenger.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E6-Gardermoen-Moelv|title=Om E6 Gardermoen - Moelv {{!}} E6 Gardermoen-Moelv AS|website=e6bompenger.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans E6 Gardermoen-Moelv AS\n|-\n|Frya-Sjoa, Oppland<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e6ringebu-otta.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E6-Ringebu-Otta|title=Om E6 Ringebu-Otta {{!}} E6 Ringebu-Otta AS|website=e6ringebu-otta.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans Ringebu-Otta AS\n|-\n|[[File:AB-Br\u00fccke.svg|24x24px]] [[H\u00e5logaland Bridge]]<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.haalogalandsbrua.no/Om_prosjektet-3.aspx|title=Om prosjektet {{!}} BPS Nord \u2013 H\u00e5logalandsbrua AS|website=www.haalogalandsbrua.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - H\u00e5logalandsbrua AS\n|-\n|{{Jct|country=NOR|E|6|E|10}}\n|Tr\u00e6ldal - Leirvik<ref name=\":4\" />\n|Nordland\n|BPS Nord - H\u00e5logalandsbrua AS\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |{{Europavei|16}}\n|Bolstad, Vossapakko, Hordaland<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://ferde.no/om-oss/vossapakko/|title=Bompenger Voss {{!}} AutoPass-brikke og avtale Vossapakko|website=Ferde|language=nb-NO|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Vestland\n|Ferde AS\n|-\n|Kongsvinger-Slomarka, Hedmark<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://kongsvingervegen.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E16-Kongsvingervegen|title=Om E16 Kongsvingervegen {{!}} E16 Kongsvingervegen AS|website=kongsvingervegen.vegfinans.no|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E16 Kongsvingervegen AS\n|-\n|Bagn-Bj\u00f8rgo, Oppland<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e16oppland.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E16-Oppland|title=Om E16 Oppland {{!}} E16 Oppland AS|last=|first=|date=|website=e16oppland.vegfinans.no|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-01}}</ref>\n|Innlandet\n|Vegfinans E16 Oppland AS\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |{{Europavei|18}}\n|\u00d8stfoldpakka, \u00d8stfold<ref name=\":3\" />\n|Viken\n|Vegfinans \u00d8stfold Bompengeselskap AS\n|-\n|Gulli-Langangen, Vestfold<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e18vestfold.vegfinans.no/Om-oss/Om-E18-Vestfold-AS|title=Om E18 Vestfold AS 